data-triple-N3.o: "Lancashire County Cricket Club represents the historic county of Lancashire in cricket's County Championship. Founded in 1864 as a successor to Manchester Cricket Club, Lancashire have played at Old Trafford since then and, in 1865, played their inaugural first-class match, beating Middlesex at Old Trafford. Johnny Briggs, whose career lasted from 1879 to 1900, was the first player to score 10,000runs and take 1,000wickets for Lancashire."@en
